{"title":"Shovel Research Fork Mounted Brake Cable Hanger (FMBCH) Re-Up","link":"https://theradavist.com/shovel-research-fmbch/","date":1714485482000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2400\" height=\"1600\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/gold-anodizing-small-3.jpg?fit=1200,1600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/gold-anodizing-small-3.jpg?w=2400&amp;quality=75 2400w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/gold-anodizing-small-3.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/gold-anodizing-small-3.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/gold-anodizing-small-3.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/gold-anodizing-small-3.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/gold-anodizing-small-3.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Shovel Research has been dissatisfied with the commonly available fork-mounted cable hangers and this is the answer: <a href=\"https://shovelresearch.com/fork-mounted-brake-cable-hanger\" target=\"_blank\">the FMBCH</a>…<span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1080\" height=\"1350\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/361771300_672280118122286_5307636894306696969_n.jpg?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/361771300_672280118122286_5307636894306696969_n.jpg?w=1080&amp;quality=75 1080w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/361771300_672280118122286_5307636894306696969_n.jpg?resize=768,960&amp;quality=75 768w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1080\" height=\"1350\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/361890788_1966906867006509_7937280101892293581_n.jpg?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/361890788_1966906867006509_7937280101892293581_n.jpg?w=1080&amp;quality=75 1080w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/361890788_1966906867006509_7937280101892293581_n.jpg?resize=768,960&amp;quality=75 768w\" /></p>\n<p>It mounts to your fork crown hole and provides enough height to properly set up wide profile cantis. For those with a long distance from the headset to the cable carrier, this offers a more rigid hanger solution, while for those with very short headtubes this may simplify cable routing that would otherwise need a tight turn. For everyone, it minimizes cable rub when you use a front bag.</p>\n<p>It has some drilled and tapped speed holes for <i>the look</i>, as well as a slot for lightness. CNC’d by Shove Research in Portland, Oregon. Pairs well with the <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/shovel-research-rod-steward-review/\" target=\"_blank\">Rod Steward</a> bag support, too!</p>\n<p><strong>Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Material: 6061-T6 aluminum</li>\n<li>Weight: 23g (28g with brass adjuster)</li>\n<li>Finish: anodized (black, silver, or gold)</li>\n<li>Logo lasered on under side</li>\n</ul>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://shovelresearch.com/fork-mounted-brake-cable-hanger\" target=\"_blank\">Shovel Research</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/shovel-research-fmbch/\">Shovel Research Fork Mounted Brake Cable Hanger (FMBCH) Re-Up</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"0b4398c439911e4fc8f4968256ab68078b1a49512254e1062485095f66dca759","category":"Cycling"}